The Herald Takudzwa Chitsiga Sports Reporter
NESBERT “Yabo” Saruchera’s ZIFA Northern Region Division One league leaders Cranborne Bullets have opened a huge lead after beating Blue Jets on Saturday. They now have an eight-point lead over Black Mambas. Meanwhile, the ZIFA Northern Region Soccer League are mourning the death of Blue Swallows midfielder, Walter Mudavanhu, who passed away yesterday morning at Manyame Airbase Clinic. In a statement the league said they were deeply saddened by the death of the footballer. ZIFA Northern Region Results Karoi United 1, Chegutu Pirates 1; Beta XI 1, Banket United 1; PAM United 0, Kariba Waves 0; Cranborne Bullets 2, Blue Jets 1; FC Mbare National 0, Black Tigers 1; Herentals U-20 2, CAM and Motor 2. Central Region Results FC Platinum 2, Whawha 0; The Venue 0, MSU 3; Vumbachikwe 1, Shabanie 0; Filabusi United 1, Blaket Mine 3; Sheasham 5, Gokwe North 0; ZPC Munyati 3, Kwekwe United 1; Dendairy 4, Black Eagles 1; ZRP Gweru 1, Dulibadzimu United 1; Real BVM 2, Ivan Hoe Mine 2. Central Region Log G       W       D       L       F        A        Pts Sheasham                   19      14       2       3       31      8        44 ZPC Munyati                 20      13       3       4       35      14      42 Vumbachikwe               20      12       5       3       28      17      41 MSU                          20      11       7       2       24      9        40 Whawha                     20      10       5       5       27      14      35 Ivan Hoe Mine              20      9        7       4       29      16      34 FC Platinum U-19          20      9        6       5       21      17      33 Dulibadzimu Utd           19      6        9       4       18      14      27 Blanket Mine                20      6        7       7       24      28      25 Gokwe North                20      6        6       8       18      30      24 Dendairy                     20      6        5       9       21      24      23 REAL BVM                    20      5        7       8       23    